"{\"uid\": \"rappler.com-sports-eiffel-tower-countdown-turns-100-days-paris-olympics-2024\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  SUMMARY  This is AI generated summarization, which may have errors.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 69, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 19, \"end\": 21, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.9533924937622263, \"rank\": 0.04888571196277802, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For context, always refer to the full article.\", \"from\": 70, \"to\": 116, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"COUNTDOWN.\", \"from\": 118, \"to\": 128, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The countdown clock near the Eiffel Tower shows 100 days to go until the Paris 2024 Olympic Games opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 129, \"to\": 244, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Benoit Tessier/REUTERS  PARIS, France - The Eiffel Tower's countdown clock to the Paris 2024 Olympics turned to 100 days on Tuesday, April 16, as preparations for the Games entered the final stage.\", \"from\": 246, \"to\": 443, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 246, \"end\": 252, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Benoit\", \"score\": 0.9989495279056572, \"rank\": 0.0010505671792558312, \"text\": \"Benoit\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Benoit\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Benoit\"}, {\"begin\": 261, \"end\": 268, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"REUTERS\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}, {\"begin\": 277, \"end\": 283, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999954245126985, \"rank\": 4.565731349614888e-06, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympic torch was lit in ancient Olympia earlier in the day.\", \"from\": 445, \"to\": 509, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 449, \"end\": 462, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_flame\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1360642986041847e-29, \"text\": \"Olympic torch\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_flame\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_flame\"}, {\"begin\": 482, \"end\": 489, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia_London\", \"score\": 0.9999999982533154, \"rank\": 1.7466591802935212e-09, \"text\": \"Olympia\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia_London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia_London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It will reach France on May 8 in the port city of Marseille, after a journey on the three-masted Belem ship.\", \"from\": 510, \"to\": 618, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 524, \"end\": 530, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999954245126985, \"rank\": 4.565731349614888e-06, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 560, \"end\": 569, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\", \"score\": 0.9999999999977263, \"rank\": 2.374687768110156e-12, \"text\": \"Marseille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\"}, {\"begin\": 607, \"end\": 612, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bel\\u00e9m\", \"score\": 0.9903282791598326, \"rank\": 0.00799898425596817, \"text\": \"Belem\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bel\\u00e9m\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bel\\u00e9m\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All permanent infrastructures for the Games are now ready, and the building of temporary sites has started in Paris, notably on the Place de la Concorde.\", \"from\": 620, \"to\": 773, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 730, \"end\": 735, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3068573029452983e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 752, \"end\": 772, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.485295316943157e-18, \"text\": \"Place de la Concorde\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Organizers will count on the flame relay across France for the mood to swing in the country as the July 26-August 11 Games approach.\", \"from\": 775, \"to\": 907, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 823, \"end\": 829, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999954245126985, \"rank\": 4.565731349614888e-06, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Last month, a poll showed that, in France, 57% of people felt little or no enthusiasm for the Paris Games.\", \"from\": 909, \"to\": 1015, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 944, \"end\": 950, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999954245126985, \"rank\": 4.565731349614888e-06, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris 2024 posters were displayed in metro stations on Tuesday and some landmark monuments paid tribute to the upcoming Games, while the stairs leading up to the Sacre Coeur basilica were being painted with the Games' colors.\", \"from\": 1017, \"to\": 1242, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1017, \"end\": 1027, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1837707896562284e-26, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1185, \"end\": 1190, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CoEur_devotional_path\", \"score\": 0.9999963428170786, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Coeur\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CoEur_devotional_path\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CoEur_devotional_path\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In ancient Olympia, Greece,the torch for the Paris 2024 Olympic Games was lit in ancient Olympia in a traditional ceremony on Tuesday, marking the final stretch of the seven-year preparation for the Games' start on July 26.\", \"from\": 1244, \"to\": 1467, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1255, \"end\": 1270, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia,_Greece\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Olympia, Greece\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia,_Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia,_Greece\"}, {\"begin\": 1255, \"end\": 1270, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia,_Greece\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Olympia, Greece\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia,_Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia,_Greece\"}, {\"begin\": 1333, \"end\": 1340, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia_London\", \"score\": 0.9999999982533154, \"rank\": 1.7466591802935212e-09, \"text\": \"Olympia\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia_London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia_London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Greek actress Mary Mina, playing the role of high priestess, lit the torch using a backup flame instead of a parabolic mirror that is normally used, due to cloudy skies, for the start of a relay in Greece and France.\", \"from\": 1469, \"to\": 1685, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1469, \"end\": 1474, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.956299251948918, \"rank\": 0.04380960791473275, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}, {\"begin\": 1667, \"end\": 1673, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.9984852388308919, \"rank\": 0.0015141906931700666, \"text\": \"Greece\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}, {\"begin\": 1678, \"end\": 1684, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999954245126985, \"rank\": 4.565731349614888e-06, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It will culminate with the lighting of the Olympic flame in the French capital at the opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 1687, \"to\": 1790, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1751, \"end\": 1757, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999864328444285, \"rank\": 9.378328418545203e-06, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris will host the summer Olympics for a third time after 1900 and 1924.\", \"from\": 1791, \"to\": 1864, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1791, \"end\": 1796, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3068573029452983e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"In these difficult times we are living through, with wars and conflicts on the rise, people are fed up with all the hate, the aggression and negative news they are facing day in and day out,\\\" International Olympic Committee (IOC) president Thomas Bach said in his speech.\", \"from\": 1866, \"to\": 2138, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2059, \"end\": 2096, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We are longing for something which brings us together, something that is unifying, something that gives us hope.\", \"from\": 2140, \"to\": 2253, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympic flame that we are lighting today is the symbol of this hope.\\\"\", \"from\": 2254, \"to\": 2327, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2258, \"end\": 2271, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_flame\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0079786178791608e-29, \"text\": \"Olympic flame\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_flame\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_flame\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The IOC has cleared the way for Russian and Belarusian athletes to compete at the Olympics despite the ongoing war in Ukraine but they will do so as neutral athletes with no national flag or anthem, a decision that angered Moscow.\", \"from\": 2329, \"to\": 2559, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2333, \"end\": 2336, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.307382343474645e-35, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 2361, \"end\": 2368, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.8279893478089884, \"rank\": 0.17376648931557545, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 2373, \"end\": 2383, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belarus\", \"score\": 0.999992734573443, \"rank\": 5.9442429852362665e-06, \"text\": \"Belarusian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belarus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belarus\"}, {\"begin\": 2447, \"end\": 2454, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.9999998690150363, \"rank\": 1.1834727102169054e-07, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}, {\"begin\": 2552, \"end\": 2558, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\", \"score\": 0.9999999987585397, \"rank\": 1.2039751229085364e-09, \"text\": \"Moscow\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"French President Emmanuel Macron also said last week Russia would be asked to observe a ceasefire in Ukraine during the Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 2561, \"to\": 2696, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2561, \"end\": 2577, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French President\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 2578, \"end\": 2593, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emmanuel Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}, {\"begin\": 2614, \"end\": 2620, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999535329102984, \"rank\": 4.617024288228335e-05, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 2662, \"end\": 2669, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.9999998690150363, \"rank\": 1.1834727102169054e-07, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Kremlin said Ukraine might use it as an opportunity to regroup and rearm.\", \"from\": 2697, \"to\": 2774, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2701, \"end\": 2708, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kremlin\", \"score\": 0.9999998871612724, \"rank\": 1.128371467500598e-07, \"text\": \"Kremlin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kremlin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kremlin\"}, {\"begin\": 2714, \"end\": 2721, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.9999998690150363, \"rank\": 1.1834727102169054e-07, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Suspending armed conflicts under an Olympic truce during the Games was a standard practice in ancient Greece.\", \"from\": 2776, \"to\": 2885, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2870, \"end\": 2884, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"score\": 0.999999999951342, \"rank\": 4.437364273541367e-11, \"text\": \"ancient Greece\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The high priestess then lit the torch of the first runner of the relay, Greece's Olympic rowing champion Stefanos Ntouskos.\", \"from\": 2887, \"to\": 3010, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2992, \"end\": 3009, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stefanos_Ntouskos\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stefanos Ntouskos\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stefanos_Ntouskos\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stefanos_Ntouskos\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After a short run he then handed the flame on to France's three-time Olympic medallist in swimming and head of Paris' Olympic torch relay, Laure Manaudou, as the representative of the host city.\", \"from\": 3012, \"to\": 3206, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3061, \"end\": 3067, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999954245126985, \"rank\": 4.565731349614888e-06, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 3123, \"end\": 3128, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3068573029452983e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 3151, \"end\": 3165, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laure_Manaudou\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Laure Manaudou\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laure_Manaudou\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laure_Manaudou\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The flame will be officially handed over to Paris Games organizers in Athens's Panathenaic stadium, site of the first modern Games in 1896, on April 26 after an 11-day relay across Greece.\", \"from\": 3208, \"to\": 3396, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3278, \"end\": 3284, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athens\", \"score\": 0.9984400930442845, \"rank\": 0.0015623440669062106, \"text\": \"Athens\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athens\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athens\"}, {\"begin\": 3287, \"end\": 3298, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Panathenaic_Games\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Panathenaic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Panathenaic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Panathenaic_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 3389, \"end\": 3395, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.9984852388308919, \"rank\": 0.0015141906931700666, \"text\": \"Greece\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It will then depart the next day for France on board a three-masted ship, the Belem, where it will arrive on May 8 in Marseille, with up to 150,000 people expected to attend the ceremony in the southern city's Old Port.\", \"from\": 3398, \"to\": 3617, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3435, \"end\": 3441, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999954245126985, \"rank\": 4.565731349614888e-06, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 3476, \"end\": 3481, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bel\\u00e9m\", \"score\": 0.9903282791598326, \"rank\": 0.00799898425596817, \"text\": \"Belem\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bel\\u00e9m\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bel\\u00e9m\"}, {\"begin\": 3516, \"end\": 3525, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\", \"score\": 0.9999999999977263, \"rank\": 2.374687768110156e-12, \"text\": \"Marseille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The last torch bearer in Marseille will climb on the roof of the Velodrome stadium on May 9, organizers said.\", \"from\": 3619, \"to\": 3728, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3644, \"end\": 3653, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\", \"score\": 0.9999999999977263, \"rank\": 2.374687768110156e-12, \"text\": \"Marseille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Marseille, founded by the Greek settlers of Phocaea around 600 BC, will host the sailing competitions.\", \"from\": 3730, \"to\": 3832, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3730, \"end\": 3739, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\", \"score\": 0.9999999999977263, \"rank\": 2.374687768110156e-12, \"text\": \"Marseille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\"}, {\"begin\": 3756, \"end\": 3761, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.956299251948918, \"rank\": 0.04380960791473275, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}, {\"begin\": 3793, \"end\": 3795, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anno_Domini\", \"score\": 0.8564785380920514, \"rank\": 0.16624379876920145, \"text\": \"BC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anno_Domini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anno_Domini\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French torch relay will last 68 days and will end in Paris with the lighting of the Olympic flame on July 26.- Rappler.com  How does this make you feel?\", \"from\": 3834, \"to\": 3990, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3838, \"end\": 3844, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999864328444285, \"rank\": 9.378328418545203e-06, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 3891, \"end\": 3896, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3068573029452983e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"follow us\", \"from\": 3992, \"to\": 4001, \"entities\": []}]}"